data.name: Listing subscriptions
Accept
data.description: if you want to retrieve entries in json format (for feeds only!), similar to using the query string header format=json

data.name: after
data.description: The id of an entry in the feed. The response will only include entries published after this one.

data.name: before
data.description: The id of an entry in the feed. The response will only include entries published before this one.

data.name: callback
data.description: This will render the entries as a JSONP.

data.name: count
data.description: Optional number of items you want to retrieve. Current max is 50 and default is 10.

data.name: format
data.description: json if you want to retrieve entries in json format (for feeds only!).

data.name: hub.callback
data.description: The value can either be a callback with which you are subscribed to one or more feeds or a search query that should match one or more callback urls used to subscribed to several feeds. Please, use the query syntax used to search for subscriptions. In both cases, make sure there are less than 200 matching feeds.

data.name: hub.topic
data.description: The URL of the HTTP resource for which you want the past entries.
This call allows you to retrieve past entries from one or more feeds. Note that you need to be subscribed to the feed(s) in order to do this.
data.name: Retrieving Past Content
Accept
data.description: This will create a 'json' subscription, similar to using the query string format=json.

data.name: format
data.description: * json if you want to receive notifications as json format (for feeds only!).  * atom if you explicitly want to receive notification as Atom. This is used by default for any resource that's either Atom or RSS.     If you don't specify any, we will send you the data pulled from the HTTP resource, (excluding feeds).

data.name: hub.callback
data.description: The webhook: it's the URL to which notifications will be sent. Make sure you it's web-accessible, ie not behind a firewall.

data.name: hub.secret
data.description: A unique secret string which will be used by us to compute a signature. You should check this signature when getting notifications.

data.name: hub.topic
data.description: The URL of the HTTP resource to which you want to subscribe.

data.name: hub.verify
data.description: sync or async: will perform a PubSubHubbub verification of intent synschronously or asynschronously.

data.name: retrieve
data.description: If set to true, the response will include the current representation of the feed as stored in Superfeedr, in the format desired. Please check our Schema for more details.

data.name: hub-callback
data.description: The URL to which notifications will be sent. It is optional if you are only subscribed to the feed 'once', with a single hub.callback. If you have multiple subscriptions, you will need to supply the hub.callback parameter. It is also required if you use the hub.verify param.

data.name: hub.topic
data.description: The URL of the HTTP resource to which you want to subscribe.

data.name: hub.verify
data.description: sync or async. We will perform a PubSubHubbub verification of intent synschronously or asynschronously.

description: Superfeedr allows you to subscribe to content on the web, and receive push notifications in real-time when new content is published. It also allows you to retrieve past content, and we’ve also got a range of normalization options that make for easier consumption.
